  "prompt": "Who is the best actor in world?",
  "response": "The title of \"best actor in the world\" is subjective and can vary depending on personal opinions, criteria, and cultural perspectives. However, there are several actors who are frequently celebrated for their exceptional talent, versatility, and contributions to the film industry. Some of these actors include:\n\n1. **Meryl Streep** - Often regarded as one of the greatest actresses of her generation, Streep has received numerous accolades, including three Academy Awards and a record 21 Oscar nominations.\n\n2. **Daniel Day-Lewis** - Known for his intense method acting and versatility, Day-Lewis has won three Academy Awards for Best Actor and is often praised for his transformative performances.\n\n3. **Leonardo DiCaprio** - With a career spanning decades, DiCaprio has delivered powerful performances in a wide range of films, earning him an Academy Award for Best Actor for *The Revenant* (2015).\n\n4. **Cate Blanchett** - Renowned for her versatility and ability to embody a wide range of characters, Blanchett has won two Academy Awards and numerous other accolades.\n\n5. **Tom Hanks** - A beloved actor known for his everyman appeal and emotional depth, Hanks has won two Academy Awards and is celebrated for roles in classics like *Forrest Gump* and *Cast Away*.\n\n6. **Viola Davis** - Known for her powerful and emotional performances, Davis has won an Academy Award, an Emmy, and two Tony Awards, making her one of the few artists to achieve the \"Triple Crown of Acting.\"\n\n7. **Anthony Hopkins** - With a career spanning over six decades, Hopkins is celebrated for his iconic roles, including Hannibal Lecter in *The Silence of the Lambs*, for which he won an Academy Award.\n\n8. **Joaquin Phoenix** - Known for his intense and transformative performances, Phoenix won an Academy Award for Best Actor for his role in *Joker* (2019).\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" actor can vary depending on personal taste and the specific qualities one values in a performer.",
